{"word":"educere","priority":"☆☆☆","meanings":[{"part_of_speech":"verb","definition":"(ラテン語)引き出す、導き出す、引き出す、連れ出す","english_definition":"(Latin) to lead forth, draw out, bring out, lead away.","examples":[{"sentence":"Animum a corpore educere.","translation":"魂を肉体から引き離す。"},{"sentence":"Coloniam in agrum educere.","translation":"植民地を土地に送り出す。"}],"collocations":[],"synonyms":["producere","extrahere","exducere"],"antonyms":["inducere","introducere"]}],"etymology":{"value":"ラテン語の「ē-」(外へ) + 「dūcere」(導く)から構成される。","priority":"★★★"},"pronunciation":{"ipa":"/eːˈduːkɛre/","syllables":"e-du-ce-re"},"inflection":{"verb_forms":{"present_infinitive":"educere","perfect_infinitive":"eduxisse","present_participle":"educens","future_participle":"educturus","perfect_participle":"edictus","gerund":"educendum","gerundive":"educendus"},"conjugation_examples":{"present_active":{"1st_person_singular":"educō","2nd_person_singular":"educis","3rd_person_singular":"educit","1st_person_plural":"educimus","2nd_person_plural":"educitis","3rd_person_plural":"educunt"},"imperfect_active":{"1st_person_singular":"educēbam","2nd_person_singular":"educēbās","3rd_person_singular":"educēbat","1st_person_plural":"educēbāmus","2nd_person_plural":"educēbātis","3rd_person_plural":"educēbant"},"future_active":{"1st_person_singular":"educam","2nd_person_singular":"educēs","3rd_person_singular":"educet","1st_person_plural":"educēmus","2nd_person_plural":"educētis","3rd_person_plural":"educent"},"perfect_active":{"1st_person_singular":"edūxī","2nd_person_singular":"edūxistī","3rd_person_singular":"edūxit","1st_person_plural":"edūximus","2nd_person_plural":"edūxistis","3rd_person_plural":"edūxērunt"},"pluperfect_active":{"1st_person_singular":"edūxeram","2nd_person_singular":"edūxerās","3rd_person_singular":"edūxerat","1st_person_plural":"edūxerāmus","2nd_person_plural":"edūxerātis","3rd_person_plural":"edūxerant"},"future_perfect_active":{"1st_person_singular":"edūxerō","2nd_person_singular":"edūxeris","3rd_person_singular":"edūxerit","1st_person_plural":"edūxerimus","2nd_person_plural":"edūxeritis","3rd_person_plural":"edūxerint"}}},"usage_notes":{"explanation":"「educere」は古典ラテン語の動詞で、物理的に何かを外に「引き出す」という意味のほかに、抽象的に人の能力や性質を「引き出す」「導き出す」という意味合いも持ちます。英語の「educate」の語源となった単語です。","priority":"★★☆"},"common_mistakes":{},"related_words":{"derivatives":["ēductio (名詞: 引き出し、導出)","ēductor (名詞: 引き出す人、導く人)","educatio (名詞: 教育、育成) - 英語の education の語源","educo (動詞: 私は引き出す) - 一人称単数現在形"]},"level_frequency":{},"readability_explanation":{"level":"C2","text":"「educere」はラテン語の動詞であり、現代の英語話者には直接的な意味は持ちません。しかし、英語の「educate」の語源であることを理解すると、教育の本質が単に知識を詰め込むだけでなく、潜在能力を「引き出す」ことにあるという洞察が得られます。ラテン語の知識がある人にとっては、文章の構造や他の単語との関連性から意味を推測できます。"},"example_sentences":[{"sentence":"Deus ex machina personam ex scaena educit.","translation":"デウス・エクス・マキナが舞台から人物を連れ出す。","type":"verb","meaning_category":"引き出す、連れ出す"},{"sentence":"Philosophia veritatem ex obscuritate educit.","translation":"哲学は真実を暗闇から引き出す。","type":"verb","meaning_category":"引き出す、導き出す"}]}